# NOTICE

This project is a **Snowflake port** of the Databricks-based **sap-bdc-mcp-server**
by Mario DeFelipe (MIT License):

    https://github.com/MarioDeFelipe/sap-bdc-mcp-server

The original implementation targets Databricks (Unity Catalog, Delta Sharing
recipients, `databricks-sdk`, `sap-bdc-connect-sdk`). This derivative work
re-implements the same 17-tool surface against **Snowflake** technologies —
specifically the **SAP BDC Connect zero-copy connector** (`ZEROCOPY CONNECTOR
... PARTNER = SAP_BDC`), Snowflake shares, and catalog-linked databases — and is
designed to run as an MCP server inside **Cortex Code**.

Substantial portions of the platform-neutral logic (SAP-Note diagnostic rules,
ORD metadata validation, tenant-hostname validation, CSN handling) are ported
faithfully from the original. See `docs/CONVERSION.md` for the full
Databricks → Snowflake mapping.

